20/06/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) --SFOR troops have increased regular patrolling along the BiH border with Serbia-Montenegro, spokesperson Mark Hope said Friday (18 June). 
He said the increase was intended to help fight crime.
In other news, the chairman of the BiH Council of Ministers said his country has made significant progress in meeting 16 recommendations of the 2004 European Commission Stabilisation and Association Reports for the Western Balkans. 
Adnan Terzic said Friday that he believes BiH would succeed in making the reforms needed to obtain approval for starting talks on the Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU this year. 
(FENA, Makfax - 18/06/04)
